# Deepsuck Harness — Data Model

> The harness is the runtime container that enforces DAG-first behavior. SOUL.md is the constitution. These entities define what the harness tracks and enforces.

---

## Core Entities

### Entity: SOUL

The constitution file loaded at agent startup as system prompt prefix.

```yaml
entity: SOUL
type: entity
properties:
  path:
    type: string
    required: true
  lines:
    type: number
    required: true
  chars:
    type: number
    required: true
  tokens_est:
    type: number
    required: true
  dynamic:
    type: boolean
    required: true
  position:
    type: enum
    values: [system_prompt_prefix]
    required: true
states: [loaded, enforced]
lifecycle: loaded → enforced
```

### Entity: AuditTrapdoor

Self-audit that fires every 5 tool calls. Four diagnostic questions. Failure forces DAG reload.

```yaml
entity: AuditTrapdoor
type: entity
properties:
  trigger:
    type: enum
    values: [every_5_tool_calls]
    required: true
  question_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  fail_action:
    type: enum
    values: [reload_dag, block_response]
    required: true
states: [idle, triggered, passed, failed]
lifecycle: idle → triggered → passed → idle
```

### Entity: ConfidenceMarker

Appended to every code answer. Measures grounding against DAG entities.

```yaml
entity: ConfidenceMarker
type: entity
properties:
  format:
    type: string
    required: true
  threshold_grounded:
    type: number
    required: true
  threshold_partial:
    type: number
    required: true
states: [appended, verified]
lifecycle: appended → verified
```

### Entity: HardBlock

Immutable guardrail. Five walls. No exceptions. No workarounds.

```yaml
entity: HardBlock
type: entity
properties:
  count:
    type: number
    required: true
  enforcement:
    type: enum
    values: [absolute]
    required: true
  walls:
    type: string[]
    required: true
states: [active, violated]
lifecycle: active
```

### Entity: CompoundingLoop

Feedback loop: compile → validate → score report. Regression = block.

```yaml
entity: CompoundingLoop
type: entity
properties:
  trigger:
    type: enum
    values: [spec_file_edited]
    required: true
  commands:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  block_on_regression:
    type: boolean
    required: true
states: [idle, running, blocked]
lifecycle: idle → running → idle
```

### Entity: ToolRouter

Routing table for tool selection. Never grep for structure.

```yaml
entity: ToolRouter
type: entity
properties:
  rule_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  anti_pattern:
    type: string
    required: true
states: [enforcing]
lifecycle: enforcing
```

### Entity: Compile

The compilation process. Reads .dog files, produces .dag.

```yaml
entity: Compile
type: event
properties:
  source_files:
    type: number
    required: true
  output_hash:
    type: string
    required: true
  token_savings_pct:
    type: number
    required: false
states: [running, completed, failed]
lifecycle: running → completed
```

### Entity: DAG

Compiled spec graph. Deterministic JSON. Queryable by AI agents.

```yaml
entity: DAG
type: entity
properties:
  version:
    type: string
    required: true
  sha256:
    type: string
    required: true
  source_files:
    type: number
    required: true
  token_savings_pct:
    type: number
    required: false
states: [current, stale]
lifecycle: current → stale
```

### Entity: ExternalConfidenceVerification

Verifies [DAG: X/10] markers against actual tool call evidence. The harness evaluates the model — the model does not grade itself.

```yaml
entity: ExternalConfidenceVerification
type: entity
properties:
  evaluation_target:
    type: enum
    values: [confidence_marker]
    required: true
  evidence_source:
    type: enum
    values: [tool_call_history]
    required: true
  lie_action:
    type: enum
    values: [force_dag_reload, reset_markers, flag_response]
    required: true
  speculation_threshold:
    type: number
    required: true
states: [idle, evaluating, passed, failed]
lifecycle: idle → evaluating → passed → idle
```

### Entity: ProactiveDAGRefresh

Forces DAG re-read before code-affecting actions. Prevents drift before it happens, rather than catching it after.

```yaml
entity: ProactiveDAGRefresh
type: entity
properties:
  trigger_actions:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  pre_read_file:
    type: boolean
    required: true
  pre_write_file:
    type: boolean
    required: true
  pre_terminal:
    type: boolean
    required: true
states: [idle, refreshing, current]
lifecycle: idle → refreshing → current → idle
```

### Entity: ToolGate

Code-level physical enforcement. The tool refuses — no negotiation, no persuasion, no bypass via prompt engineering.

```yaml
entity: ToolGate
type: entity
properties:
  gate_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  enforcement_level:
    type: enum
    values: [physical, prompt]
    required: true
  gates:
    type: string[]
    required: true
states: [active, bypassed]
lifecycle: active
```

### Entity: AgentInTheMiddle

Three-role separation: Orchestrator (routes), Implementer (generates), Validator (checks). No role evaluates its own output.

```yaml
entity: AgentInTheMiddle
type: entity
properties:
  role_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  orchestrator_duties:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  implementer_duties:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  validator_duties:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  transition_rules:
    type: string[]
    required: true
states: [orchestrating, implementing, validating]
lifecycle: orchestrating → implementing → validating → orchestrating
```

---

## Relationships

### Relationship: Compile → DAG

```yaml
relationship: Compile → DAG
verb: produces
cardinality: 1:1
required: false
cascade: nullify
invariants: DAG is compiled output of all .dog files
```

### Relationship: SOUL → DAG

```yaml
relationship: SOUL → DAG
verb: references
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: SOUL.md truth hierarchy starts with DAG. No code read before DAG load
```

### Relationship: AuditTrapdoor → DAG

```yaml
relationship: AuditTrapdoor → DAG
verb: queries
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Trapdoor must re-read .dag on failure. No proceeding without DAG verification
```

### Relationship: ExternalConfidenceVerification → ConfidenceMarker

```yaml
relationship: ExternalConfidenceVerification → ConfidenceMarker
verb: validates
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: External verification checks marker claims against tool call evidence. Model cannot grade itself.
```

### Relationship: ProactiveDAGRefresh → DAG

```yaml
relationship: ProactiveDAGRefresh → DAG
verb: refreshes
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: DAG must be re-read before any code-affecting action. No stale memory.
```

### Relationship: ToolGate → HardBlock

```yaml
relationship: ToolGate → HardBlock
verb: implements
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Tool gates are the physical enforcement of hard blocks. Prompt walls become code walls.
```

### Relationship: AgentInTheMiddle → ToolRouter

```yaml
relationship: AgentInTheMiddle → ToolRouter
verb: routes_through
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Orchestrator uses tool routing table to dispatch to implementer vs validator roles.
```

### Relationship: AgentInTheMiddle → CompoundingLoop

```yaml
relationship: AgentInTheMiddle → CompoundingLoop
verb: triggers
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: After implementation, AgentInTheMiddle triggers CompoundingLoop to validate before reporting.
```

### Entity: IntelligenceEngine

Executable scripts implementing published reasoning techniques — Tree of Thoughts, Reflexion, Knowledge Fetch, DSPy Optimization. Bridges v4 Pro to frontier-model tier.

```yaml
entity: IntelligenceEngine
type: entity
properties:
  technique_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  tot_source:
    type: string
    required: true
  reflexion_source:
    type: string
    required: true
  dspy_source:
    type: string
    required: true
  script_path:
    type: string
    required: true
states: [idle, executing, complete]
lifecycle: idle → executing → complete → idle
```

### Relationship: IntelligenceEngine → SOUL

```yaml
relationship: IntelligenceEngine → SOUL
verb: implements
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Intelligence Engine scripts are the executable implementation of SOUL.md Intelligence Bootstrap section. SOUL says what. Engine does how.
```

### Entity: HookEnforcement

Code-level enforcement via collar shell hooks. Fires on pre_llm_call, transform_llm_output, post_tool_call, and on_session_end. The model cannot skip these — they execute regardless of LLM compliance.

```yaml
entity: HookEnforcement
type: entity
properties:
  hook_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  events:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  enforcement_level:
    type: enum
    values: [code_level, prompt_level]
    required: true
  auto_accept:
    type: boolean
    required: true
states: [configured, active, blocked]
lifecycle: configured → active
```

### Relationship: HookEnforcement → IntelligenceEngine

```yaml
relationship: HookEnforcement → IntelligenceEngine
verb: executes
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Hooks are the code-level execution of IntelligenceEngine techniques. Scripts in ~/.dag/skills/intelligence-engine/hooks/
```

### Relationship: HookEnforcement → ToolGate

```yaml
relationship: HookEnforcement → ToolGate
verb: complements
cardinality: 1:1
required: false
cascade: restrict
invariants: ToolGates block bad actions. HookEnforcement injects intelligence. Both are code-level. Neither depends on LLM compliance.
```
